wmii-dialog - notification dialog for wmii
==========================================
wmii-dialog is a notification dialog created for wmii. Although, it
has no technical dependencies to wmii, and can indeed be used in any
other window manger environment, but it's designed to suit wmii.

wmii-dialog is based on dmenu, created by Anselm R. Garbe,
Sander van Dijk and Micha≈Ç Janeczek.

wmii-dialog is not an official component of wmii.


Requirements
------------
In order to build wmii-dialog you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (wmii-dialog is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install wmii-dialog
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running wmii-dialog
-------------
See the man page for details.
